Appendix B: Complete Proofs of Detachment Theorems and Lemmas

B.1 Proof of Theorem 1 (Existence of Detachment Voltage)

Theorem 1. For any dust particle with charge q>0 and adhesion force F_{\text{adh}}>0, there exists a threshold voltage V_{\text{crit}} = \frac{2\mu_s F_{\text{adh}}}{q k (1 + \mu_s z/d_{\text{ins}})} such that for all V_0 > V_{\text{crit}}, the particle detaches.

Proof. The detachment condition is:

\langle F_{x,\text{EDS}} \rangle > \mu_s \left( F_{\text{adh}} - \langle F_{z,\text{EDS}} \rangle \right).

Substituting \langle F_{x,\text{EDS}} \rangle = \frac{1}{2} q V_0 k and \langle F_{z,\text{EDS}} \rangle = \frac{1}{2} q V_0 k \frac{z}{d_{\text{ins}}}:

\frac{1}{2} q V_0 k > \mu_s \left( F_{\text{adh}} - \frac{1}{2} q V_0 k \frac{z}{d_{\text{ins}}} \right).

Multiply both sides by 2:

q V_0 k > 2\mu_s F_{\text{adh}} - \mu_s q V_0 k \frac{z}{d_{\text{ins}}}.

Bring the term containing V_0 on the left:

q V_0 k + \mu_s q V_0 k \frac{z}{d_{\text{ins}}} > 2\mu_s F_{\text{adh}},

q V_0 k \left(1 + \mu_s \frac{z}{d_{\text{ins}}}\right) > 2\mu_s F_{\text{adh}}.

Solve for V_0:

V_0 > \frac{2\mu_s F_{\text{adh}}}{q k \left(1 + \mu_s z/d_{\text{ins}}\right)}.

Define the right-hand side as V_{\text{crit}}. Since all parameters are finite and positive, such V_0 exists. ∎

