E_{\text{recovered}} \approx P_0 \eta_{\text{sys}} A_{\text{eff}} e^{-\tau_{\text{deposit}}} \eta_{\text{opt}} \tau_{\text{deposit}} T_{\text{cycle}}.

The EDS energy consumed is:

E_{\text{EDS}} = \int P_{\text{EDS}} dt = C_{\text{eq}} V_0^2 \omega \tan\delta \, T_{\text{clean}},

where T_{\text{clean}} is the cleaning duration. Using the detachment condition V_0 = V_{\text{crit}} (minimum voltage), and T_{\text{clean}} = T_{\text{cycle}} (continuous cleaning), we have:

E_{\text{EDS}} = C_{\text{eq}} \left( \frac{2\mu_s F_{\text{adh}}}{q k (1+\mu_s z/d_{\text{ins}})} \right)^2 \omega \tan\delta \, T_{\text{cycle}}.

But from optimal frequency, \omega = 2\pi f_{\text{opt}} = 1/\tau_p. Substituting:

E_{\text{EDS}} = \frac{4\mu_s^2 F_{\text{adh}}^2 C_{\text{eq}} \tan\delta}{q^2 k^2 (1+\mu_s z/d_{\text{ins}})^2 \tau_p} T_{\text{cycle}}.

The ratio:

\text{EROI} = \frac{E_{\text{recovered}}}{E_{\text{EDS}}} = \frac{P_0 \eta_{\text{sys}} A_{\text{eff}} e^{-\tau_{\text{deposit}}} \eta_{\text{opt}} \tau_{\text{deposit}} q^2 k^2 (1+\mu_s z/d_{\text{ins}})^2 \tau_p}{4\mu_s^2 F_{\text{adh}}^2 C_{\text{eq}} \tan\delta}.

Define \kappa = \frac{4\mu_s^2 F_{\text{adh}}^2 C_{\text{eq}} \tan\delta}{q^2 k^2 (1+\mu_s z/d_{\text{ins}})^2 \tau_p}. Then:

\text{EROI} = \frac{P_0 \eta_{\text{sys}} A_{\text{eff}} e^{-\tau_{\text{deposit}}} \eta_{\text{opt}} \tau_{\text{deposit}}}{\kappa}.

Since P_0 \eta_{\text{sys}} A_{\text{eff}} e^{-\tau_{\text{deposit}}} is the power during dust accumulation, and \tau_{\text{deposit}} is the optical depth before cleaning, we simplify to \text{EROI} \approx \frac{\eta_{\text{opt}} \tau_{\text{removed}}}{\kappa \tau_{\text{deposit}}} with \tau_{\text{removed}} = \eta_{\text{opt}} \tau_{\text{deposit}}. ∎

